Old Country
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:[AND 1834] constr THE: Britain; one's MOTHER COUNTRY (cf. Home, (the) Old Dart, Old Land -->(Never as frequent as HOME: tends to be have been used by immigrants)
